      },
      "date": "2013-05-04 06:41:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAlex, I has asked the same question in an earlier inspection (before it was split into two patches):\n\n However, the issues pointed out in the previous inspection should\n still be addressed. In particular, moving the sync start to be after the\n current RPC is processed instead of before it would be a good idea.\n\nAnd previous commenst from Brian in the bug:\n This soft sync can be handled asynchronously and the\n servers may optionally ignore it if they are already in\n the process of a sync. The ability to ignore the sync is\n particularly import for the ZFS OSDs to avoid thrashing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
