      "date": "2013-12-05 15:40:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nI'm a little weary of this, but without testing to prove it's right or wrong, I'm going to go ahead and give it my approval.\n\nI think we can simply set the default to \"1\" and get essentially the same behavior we've been running with in production for awhile.\n\nAnd I apologize for not giving this the attention its been needing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "db409cbdb04d1f23733e9e8b609a3ad23582bcde",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-12-06 06:06:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(3 inline comments)\n\nI think it's good to have this \"so many sync requests before actual sync\" logic. But we really need to close some holes in it:\nSo should not let a client to issue multiple requests and have them all count and also the issue that Prakash noticed where another client can cancel out a softsync sent by this client.\n\n\nGranted, I do not think this is going to be a comprehensive solution, but it's good as a first clutch.\n\nEventually I hope we can actually predict how much time is left until next sync and how many clients are actually actuvely writing, to be smarter and let a single client to actually trigger syncs at will if it's the only writer, for example.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "6910f315dc51274d8a36e9d86553caee7bc7c9e6",
